of
the
fire
in
which
I
wasted.
Presumptuous
I
never
have
been;
presumptuous
I
never
will
be.
Rather
than
even
seem
selfish
and
interested,
I
would
resolutely
rise,
gird
my
loins,
part
and
leave
her,
and
seek,
on
